---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import {
  SERIES_START,
  SERIES_END,
  SERIES_RANGE,
  SERIES_EPOCH_COUNT,
  LATEST_NCR_PCT,
  NCR_LGU_COUNT,
  MODEL_R2,
} from "../lib/series";
import CanopyTrend from "../components/CanopyTrend.astro";
const pctWhole = Math.floor(LATEST_NCR_PCT);
const pctFrac = LATEST_NCR_PCT.toFixed(2).split(".")[1];
---
<Base title="Leaves.PH · Metro Manila canopy report" pathname="/">

  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pt-10 pb-6">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-12 gap-y-8 items-end">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker mb-5">METRO MANILA · TREE-COVER MEASUREMENT SERIES</p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-ink-900 leading-[0.92] tracking-[-0.025em] text-balance"
            style="font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5.4vw, 4.25rem);">
          Tree canopy across the National Capital Region, measured from <span class="text-forest-700 font-display">Sentinel-2</span> imagery.
        </h1>
        <p class="font-sans text-[15px] text-ink-700 mt-5 leading-[1.55] max-w-[55ch]">
          {NCR_LGU_COUNT} LGUs, {SERIES_EPOCH_COUNT} annual epochs from {SERIES_START} to {SERIES_END}. Inputs, thresholds, and aggregation are committed; outputs are hash-pinned and reproducible from a clean clone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-l-2 border-ink-900 pl-5 sm:pl-7 pt-2 max-w-[28ch]">
        <p class="kicker mb-2 text-sepia-500">AREA-WEIGHTED CANOPY · NCR · LATEST EPOCH</p>
        <p class="stat-hero">{pctWhole}·{pctFrac}<span class="text-umber-500">%</span></p>
        <dl class="mt-5 space-y-2 text-[13px] font-mono tabular-nums leading-[1.5]">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between"><dt class="text-sepia-500">Method</dt><dd class="text-ink-700">NDVI &gt; 0·62</dd></div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between"><dt class="text-sepia-500">Reference</dt><dd class="text-ink-700">Meta v2 · 1 m</dd></div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between"><dt class="text-sepia-500">Boundaries</dt><dd class="text-ink-700">PSA · {NCR_LGU_COUNT} LGUs</dd></div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between"><dt class="text-sepia-500">Series</dt><dd class="text-ink-700">{SERIES_RANGE}</dd></div>
        </dl>

        <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-ink-900">
          <p class="kicker mb-2 text-forest-700">DETECTION MODEL · IN OPTIMIZATION</p>
          <p class="font-display font-medium text-forest-700 leading-none tabular-nums" style="font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4.2vw, 3.25rem);">R<sup class="text-[0.5em] align-super">2</sup>&nbsp;{MODEL_R2.toFixed(2)}</p>
          <p class="font-sans text-[12px] text-ink-700 mt-2 leading-[1.5] max-w-[34ch]">
            Canopy fraction vs Meta's 1 m reference, on held-out locations. The detection model is being optimized toward a first release; published figures use the NDVI baseline.
          </p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───── LEDE - bleeds to the left edge, marginal note hangs in the gutter ───── -->
  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pb-10">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,7fr)_minmax(0,3fr)] gap-x-12 lg:gap-x-16">
      <article class="max-w-[60ch] text-[17px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-900">
        <p class="dropcap">
          This report measures tree canopy in Metro Manila using Sentinel-2 surface-reflectance imagery, aggregated to the seventeen LGUs of the National Capital Region defined by PSA. Canopy is classified at the pixel level by NDVI greater than zero point six two, a threshold calibrated against Meta's v2 one-metre canopy-height reference at heights greater than five metres.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-ink-700">
          In the latest annual epoch the area-weighted canopy fraction across the NCR is <em>seven point four six per cent</em>. The same pipeline run against earlier Sentinel-2 imagery produces an annual time series; across the published series, regional canopy moves down zero point six two percentage points.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-ink-700">
          Movement is uneven across LGUs. Quezon City carries the largest absolute canopy share by area, anchored by the La Mesa watershed, UP Diliman, and the Wack Wack greens. The steepest year-over-year declines sit in Taguig, Malabon, Las Pinas, and Valenzuela. Per-LGU values for every epoch in the series are in Fig 4 and the downloadable CSV. <a href="/map" class="no-underline">Open the map →</a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-ink-700">
          Inputs, NDVI threshold derivation, and aggregation logic are documented on the methodology page. The published CSV is hash-pinned; running <code class="font-mono text-[14px]">make hash-verify</code> against a clean checkout reproduces the canonical artefact byte-for-byte.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="hidden lg:block text-sepia-500">
        <div class="marginal">
          <p class="text-ink-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-[10px] mb-1">SCOPE</p>
          <p>Seventeen LGUs of the National Capital Region (sixteen cities plus Pateros), per PSA boundaries. No barangay-level breakdown in this release.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="marginal mt-6">
          <p class="text-ink-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-[10px] mb-1">SOURCES</p>
          <p>Sentinel-2 L2A via Google Earth Engine. Meta canopy height v2 via AWS Open Data. PSA LGU boundaries via OSM mirrors. All canonical, all public.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="marginal mt-6">
          <p class="text-ink-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-[10px] mb-1">CORRECTIONS</p>
          <p>Methodology questions and LGU-level corrections via the repository issue tracker.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───── CANOPY TREND - two readings of the per-year series ───── -->
  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pb-10">
    <div class="max-w-[820px] mx-auto">
      <CanopyTrend />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-6">
    <figure class="max-w-[820px] mx-auto">
      <img
        src="/demo/remaining-canopy-satellite.gif"
        alt={`Sentinel-2 RGB satellite basemap of Metro Manila with remaining tree-cover density overlay, animated ${SERIES_START} to ${SERIES_END}. The basemap cycles each epoch; the green density layer shows where canopy persists.`}
        class="block w-full h-auto border border-ink-900"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <figcaption class="fig-caption mt-3 flex flex-wrap justify-between gap-2">
        <span><span class="dateline">FIG&nbsp;1 ·</span> {SERIES_START} → {SERIES_END} · Sentinel-2 RGB basemap · canopy density overlay · {SERIES_EPOCH_COUNT} frames</span>
        <span class="text-sepia-500">30 m pixel · on-frame value = mean canopy density (Hansen-adjusted), not the area-weighted headline</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule-ornament" />

  <!-- ───── FIG 3 - methodology cross-reference table, neutral references ───── -->
  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-3 text-sepia-500">FIG&nbsp;3 · METHODOLOGY CROSS-REFERENCE</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-ink-900 mb-3" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem); letter-spacing: -0.015em;">
      Adjacent published estimates of Metro Manila tree cover.
    </h2>
    <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.55] mb-6 max-w-[68ch]">
      Definitions differ across sources: canopy fraction versus closed-canopy area, percentage versus hectares, single-epoch versus multi-year baselines. The table lists figures as published; it is a methodology reference, not a ranking.
    </p>
    <table class="w-full text-[14px]">
      <thead class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-sepia-500 font-mono">
        <tr class="border-b border-ink-900">
          <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium">Source</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium">Figure</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium hidden sm:table-cell">Epoch</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium">Definition</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-300/60 font-sans">
        <tr>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top"><em>DENR FMB</em></td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top font-mono tabular-nums">6·00%</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">2024 release</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-ink-700">Canopy fraction (cited)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top">Global Forest Watch</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top font-mono tabular-nums">4·00%</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">2020 baseline</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-ink-700">Hansen GFC tree-cover, 30% canopy threshold</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top">Earth Journalism Network</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top font-mono tabular-nums">2,071 ha</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">2020</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-ink-700">Open-forest area (hectares)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top">Meta canopy v2</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top font-mono tabular-nums">7·50%</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">2018–20 epoch</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-ink-700">1 m canopy height &gt; 5 m</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-forest-100/40">
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top font-semibold text-forest-700">Leaves.PH</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top font-mono tabular-nums font-semibold text-forest-700">{pctWhole}·{pctFrac}%</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">latest epoch</td>
          <td class="py-3 pr-4 align-top text-ink-700">Sentinel-2 NDVI &gt; 0·62, Meta-calibrated</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="font-sans text-[12px] text-sepia-500 mt-4 leading-[1.5] max-w-[68ch]">
      For methodology, threshold derivation, and calibration details, see <a href="/methodology" class="no-underline text-umber-700">/methodology</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <!-- ───── FINDING - neutral one-line summary ───── -->
  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-6">
    <p class="kicker mb-4 text-sepia-500">FINDING</p>
    <blockquote class="pullquote">
      Quezon City carries the largest single share of NCR canopy; without it, the regional average is closer to four per cent.
    </blockquote>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule-ornament" />

  <!-- ───── PER-LGU FEATURE TABLE - numbered rows, decimal-aligned ───── -->
  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-8 grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,2.2fr)_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-12 gap-y-6 items-start">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker mb-3 text-sepia-500">FIG&nbsp;4 · NCR LGUs · LATEST EPOCH</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink-900 mb-6" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem); letter-spacing: -0.015em;">
        Quezon City alone carries the regional average.
      </h2>
      <table class="w-full text-[14px]">
        <thead class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-sepia-500 font-mono">
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-900">
            <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium w-8">№</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium">LGU</th>
            <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium">{SERIES_END}</th>
            <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium">{SERIES_START} → {String(SERIES_END).slice(-2)}</th>
            <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium hidden sm:table-cell">Area</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-300/60 font-sans">
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">01</td><td class="py-2"><em>Quezon City</em></td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">18·93%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·38pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">15,986 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">02</td><td class="py-2">Mandaluyong</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">11·19%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·28pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">1,131 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">03</td><td class="py-2">Makati</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">8·92%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-forest-700">+1·69pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">1,804 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">04</td><td class="py-2">Caloocan</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">8·80%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·96pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">5,288 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">05</td><td class="py-2">Marikina</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">6·87%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·01pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">2,265 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">06</td><td class="py-2">Taguig</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">6·47%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−2·76pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">7,932 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">07</td><td class="py-2">Valenzuela</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">5·81%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−1·39pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">4,678 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">08</td><td class="py-2">Pasig</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">5·23%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·17pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">3,067 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">09</td><td class="py-2">Las Pinas</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">5·20%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−1·47pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">3,612 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">10</td><td class="py-2">Pateros</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">4·96%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-forest-700">+1·26pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">185 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">11</td><td class="py-2">Paranaque</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">4·35%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-forest-700">+0·57pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">5,960 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">12</td><td class="py-2">Muntinlupa</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">3·77%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·74pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">6,615 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">13</td><td class="py-2">Malabon</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">3·68%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−1·54pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">1,636 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">14</td><td class="py-2">San Juan</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">2·41%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-forest-700">+0·76pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">578 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">15</td><td class="py-2">Pasay</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">2·08%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·93pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">3,388 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">16</td><td class="py-2">Manila</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">0·89%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-forest-700">+0·21pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">10,487 ha</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">17</td><td class="py-2">Navotas</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums">0·47%</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-umber-700">−0·40pp</td><td class="py-2 text-right font-mono tabular-nums text-sepia-500 hidden sm:table-cell">3,656 ha</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <aside class="lg:mt-16">
      <p class="kicker mb-3 text-sepia-500">READING GUIDE</p>
      <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.6]">
        Quezon City's 18·93 per cent is held by the La Mesa watershed, UP Diliman, and the Wack Wack greens. Pull QC out and the regional average halves.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.6] mt-4">
        <em>Manila, Navotas, Pasay</em> are structurally low: reclamation, dense urban core. Their canopy will not move with methodology choice; it is genuinely very low.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.6] mt-4">
        <em>Taguig, Malabon, Las Pinas, Valenzuela</em> are the steepest decliners across the published series. Construction-heavy southern and northern fringes.
      </p>
      <a href="/map" class="inline-block mt-5 font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-umber-700 no-underline border-b border-umber-500 hover:border-umber-700">Open the interactive map &rarr;</a>
    </aside>
  </section>
</Base>
